 <p>Cartumandua Spiritslammer
Clan Spiritslammer
"Phat Loot, No Work" - The Druid Motto</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=atrina>Atrina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/17/01 2:11:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/70/1553070.jpg?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We need a vote on Phinny</span><hr size=1> Problem with him being reservable is it'll make it a lot harder for people to complete their epics. Because the peices for epics are rare, you can kill her like 5 times and still not get what you need, problems like this and throwing a reservation system on it could cause someone to wait a long time to get whatever they need. And also because phiny onyl needs 12 people, saying that you can go on someone elses raid probably wont be much of a solution because not many people are needed, and i'm sure they'd rather take friends <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udexn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dexn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 232<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/17/01 10:21:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We need a vote on Phinny</span><hr size=1> Well, what you're saying contradicts what people who typically don't want him reserved are saying. So far, the reasoning has been since &quot;he's mostly up anyway&quot; that there's no point to having him reservable.<br>
<br>
However, I personally have tried on at least three occasions to take him down, and he's been gone. Kinda sucked, frankly. And that was BEFORE epics, when there wasn't quite the impetus to kill the guy anyway.<br>
<br>
Even if we reserved him for two days, like Cart suggests at least those people who would LIKE to reserve him can.  Yet, it would still allow the &quot;freedom&quot; for all those FCFS people to go fight over him.<br>
<br>
Sylvaen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uolimstonetooth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Olim Stonetooth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/17/01 11:53:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We need a vote on Phinny</span><hr size=1> No, no more reserving every bloody mob in game.  He's a 8 hour spawn, so all you have to do if you are thinking about killing him is to go yourself to the zone in point and see if he is there (track, wait for him to cast a spell, etc etc...). <p>Olim Stonetooth
57th Templar 'O Brell
GNV</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uolimstonetooth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Olim Stonetooth</A> at: 2/17/01 10:53:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucartumandua.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cartumandua</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tunare's Tough Love</span><br>  Posts: 593<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/17/01 5:48:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We need a vote on Phinny</span><hr size=1> <br>
Why is it that everyone has to be so polar on this issue?  What's wrong with a compromise?<br>
<br>
Why not a day or two of reservation and the rest free?  If it worked then we could turn fire giants the same way.<br>
<br>
Phinny has more posted intentions (or did) than firegiants.<br>
