52nd season Songweaver<br>
Brell Serilis<br><br>
Daealan <<a href=http://www.eqharpers.com>Harpers</a>><br>
21st season Enchanter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/udexn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dexn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 233<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/18/01 2:03:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We need a vote on Phinny</span><hr size=1> Good question, Cart.<br>
<br>
The general argument AGAINST reserving anything new is: &quot;What's next, EVERYTHING reservable?&quot; Much like they put in the most recent vote.<br>
<br>
No point or counterpoint on a given mob.. just examples about Lguk and reserving gnolls in Black Burrow as some kind of irrational scare tactic.<br>
<br>
I'd love to see just ONE rational reason why NOT to reserve Phinny for two days a week.<br>
<br>
Sylvaen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/ugaramebonhands.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garam Ebonhands</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/18/01 4:49:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We need a vote on Phinny</span><hr size=1> What is a rational reason (server wide) for making him reservable?<br>
<br>
We don't have to convince you, you have to convince us.<br>
<br>
Garam Ebonhands<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/uelcapograhnde.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ElCapo Grahnde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/18/01 7:40:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We need a vote on Phinny</span><hr size=1> Heck we've been watching and the last few &quot;Intentions&quot; posted were unable to kill Phinney.  Why allow people to &quot;Reserve it&quot;, when hes up so often.   How do you reserve something w/ an 8 hour spawn cycle?   <p><font face="Arial" size="2">
Clapto Grahnde, HMW<br></font>
<font face="Arial" size="1">
Aka ElCapo Grahnde<br>
53rd Champion<br>
Grand Norrathian Vanguard<br></font>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/udexn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dexn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 237<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/19/01 12:08:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We need a vote on Phinny</span><hr size=1> What's a rational reason. Hmm. Okay, I'll give you five for now.<br>
<br>
1. Some guilds, individuals, groups of people don't have unlimited amounts of time, and knowing that they reserved a time and Phinny is up, makes the game a LOT more reasonable and fun.<br>
<br>
2. Some guilds et al, also need more than just a few people to actually DO Phinny, so having him reserved means they aren't wasting valuable time (time IS valuable, btw) organizing a raid, and then NOT having Phinny up. They might need to gather 18 people, who knows.<br>
<br>
3. Phinny is an 8 hour spawn.  By not having him reservable, it's very, VERY possible that groups could go repeatedly to attempt Phinny, and yet, he wouldn't be up. Perhaps their windows of opportunity are verry narrow, and narrow minded people are keeping others from gaining access to this guy.<br>
<br>
4. If Phinny isn't that big of a deal to people, then why the big issue in reserving him a few days a week? What's the big deal? Isn't having Kael, Chardok, PoG, CoM, and, heck, the whole rest of the freaking server non-reserved enough?<br>
<br>
5. Just having a &quot;backup-location&quot; to raid doesn't quite cut it. There ARE few areas/mobs at a certain level range that are a challenge, and then after that, the level goes WAY up on what can be done.  Name any other 8 hour or more spawn time on a mob that isn't currently reservable that a group of 45's can do?<br>
<br>
And, btw, Garam, what's this &quot;you have to convince us&quot; crap? That's the same kind of pompous attitude that justify people thinking others are elitist.<br>
<br>
I am practically BEGGING for people to give me a reason NOT to reserve Phinny for two days, as Cart recommended as a very sensible compromise.<br>
<br>
So far, my best challengers have been McCarthyists (Seeing Pinko plots for reserving ALL mobs under every table) or just plain pompous (&quot;Prove it to us!&quot;). Well, fact is, it's been mentioned and argued many times. I'd like to see a &quot;formal&quot; discussion about it so that we can actually see what the general public thinks.<br>
<br>
Sylvaen<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch!</span><br>  Posts: 1195<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/19/01 12:40:47 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/ladun.jpg width=67 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We need a vote on Phinny</span><hr size=1> Sylvaen, this issue for me is this.  The reasons you give for reserving him could be applied to almost everything in the game.  If you can reserve Phingel with this reasoning, you can reserve everything else.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't mind having Phingel reservable a few days a week, but I'd rather see us err on the side of not reserving things than reserving them.<br>
<br>
So Yes.  Reserve Phingel on a limited basis. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune.jpg" width="315" height="200"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/udamastes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Damastes</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 168<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/19/01 5:02:51 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/Damastes?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We need a vote on Phinny</span><hr size=1> I personally don't think he should be reservable.<br>
<br>
1.  He's an epic quest mob.<br>
<br>
2.  He has an 8-12 hour random spawn time.  Meaning he can be killed at least 2 times a day, and possiblly 3.<br>
<br>
3.  He's not a very tough mob.  PreKunark a group of 4 or 5 lvl 50's could take him.<br>
<br>
4.  His loot drop rate is random as hell.  Leaning toward the shitty side.  IE He doesn't always drop a quest piece.<br>
<br>
5.  Kedge falls into the 'Underused zone' category.  Not many people tend to hunt in Kedge, and Phinny is generally up most of the time.<br>
<br>
6.  He's fairly easy to check to see if he's up.  Just wait for him to cast, use track, or invis your way there.<br>
<br>
<br>
As far as the idea of maybe only reserving him 2 days of the week, it doesn't sound to bad, BUT...<br>
<br>
Who decides which days he can be reserved on?<br>
<br>
Is he reserved for the whole day? or just a 12 hour period?<br>
<br>
How much notice do you have to give?<br>
<br>
Is there a limit on how many times you can reserve him in a given time?<br>
<br>
Do people going for thier epic pieces have precidence over people just 'raiding'?<br>
<br>
Will it be a rotation or FCFS by signup?<br>
<br>
